2Fluxury-home-products-worth-splurging-on-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Changing%20Place%20Names%20May%20Soon%20Be%20Punishable%20in%20Manipur%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18103704%2FF6AFcQWaIAIi2H2.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Using%20place%20names%20not%20authorised%20by%20the%20government%20may%20soon%20be%20a%20punishable%20offence%20in%20Manipur.%20A%20Bill%20that%20proposes%20this%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20tabled%20in%20the%20upcoming%20Manipur%20assembly%20session%2C%20as%20per%20a%20news%20report%20by%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fstrife-torn-manipur-new-law-changing-names-places-punishable-9155003%2F%5C%22%3E%20the%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%209%2C%20the%20Manipur%20government%20announced%20that%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20next%20assembly%20session%20will%20begin%20on%20February%2028.%20One%20of%20the%20Bills%20that%20the%20government%20might%20table%20during%20the%20session%20is%20titled%20the%20%E2%80%98Manipur%20Names%20of%20Places%20Bill%2C%202024%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20for%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20prepared%20by%20the%20Land%20Resources%20Department%20and%20approved%20by%20the%20state%20cabinet%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E%20news%20report%2C%20dated%20February%2011%2C%20said.%20Per%20the%20report%2C%20the%20objective%20is%20to%20establish%20%E2%80%9Can%20institutional%20mechanism%20to%20enforce%20correct%20use%20of%20names%20of%20places%E2%80%9D%20as%20well%20as%20to%20%E2%80%9Clay%20down%20procedures%20for%20giving%20names%20to%20places%2C%20and%20also%20for%20altering%20names%20of%20places%E2%80%9D.%20Per%20the%20Bill%2C%20offenders%20will%20be%20punished%20with%20a%20penalty%2C%20and%20can%20receive%20one%20to%20three%20years%20of%20imprisonment%20upon%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20new%20Bill%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98Place%20Names%20Committee%E2%80%99%20will%20be%20created%20to%20make%20recommendations%20on%20the%20names%2C%20subject%20to%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20government.%20The%20latest%20news%20report%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20proposal%20for%20the%20Act%20states%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20have%20been%20multiple%20instances%20of%20the%20use%20of%20unauthorised%20names%20of%20places%20by%20certain%20individuals%20or%20groups%20of%20people%20or%20organisations%2C%20with%20possible%20malafide%20intent%2C%20which%20had%20the%20potential%20to%20create%20confusion%20in%20the%20administration%20of%20the%20state.%E2%80%9D%20The%20proposal%20also%20lists%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccertain%20administrative%20challenges%20are%20also%20faced%20due%20to%20such%20unauthorised%20use%20of%20names%20of%20places%20at%20the%20time%20of%20discharging%20their%20duties%20by%20government%20officials%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENames%20of%20places%20have%20been%20a%20contested%20issue%20since%20violence%20began%20in%20Manipur%20in%20May%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20report%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20prominent%20example%E2%80%9D%20is%20that%20of%20the%20Kuki-Zomi-dominated%20district%20Churachandpur%20and%20its%20district%20headquarters%2C%20also%20called%20Churachandpur.%20The%20district%20and%20town%20is%20named%20after%20a%20Meitei%20king%20of%20the%20former%20Manipur%20kingdom%2C%20Churachand%20Singh%2C%20who%20ruled%20the%20area%20from%201891%20to%201941.%20But%20people%20from%20the%20Kuki-Zomi%20community%20have%20been%20calling%20the%20town%20%E2%80%9CLamka%E2%80%9D%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20Both%20the%20names%20are%20over%20a%20hundred%20years%20old%2C%20per%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20after%20the%20violence%20erupted%2C%20the%20name%20Lamka%20began%20appearing%20on%20homes%2C%20shops%20and%20even%20government%20institutions%20and%20offices.%20Similarly%2C%20resident%20Meiteis%20now%20call%20Paite%20Veng%20(Paite%20is%20a%20Zo%20sub-tribe%20and%20Veng%20means%20colony)%20in%20Imphal%20%E2%80%98Kwakeithel%20Ningthemkol%E2%80%99%20via%20a%20signboard%2C%20the%20news%20report%20highlighted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Manipur%20government%2C%20via%20an%20order%20by%20the%20chief%20secretary%2C%20told%20organisations%20and%20individuals%20to%20not%20change%20names%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdistricts%2C%20sub-divisions%2C%20places%2C%20institutions%2C%20and%20addresses%20of%20such%20institutions%E2%80%9D%20on%20their%20own%20%E2%80%93%20which%20could%20create%20possible%20conflict%20between%20communities%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fdont-change-names-of-places-warns-manipur-government%2Farticle67393496.ece%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20upcoming%20assembly%20session%20will%20be%20only%20the%20second%20so%20far%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20ethnic%20conflict%20on%20May%203%20last%20year.%20As%20per%20latest%20official%20figures%20%E2%80%93%20as%20of%20September%2015%20last%20year%20%E2%80%93%20the%20violence%20has%20killed%20175%20people%20and%20injured%201%2C118%3B%2032%20people%20are%20still%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707650780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F18103704%2FF6AFcQWaIAIi2H2.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fchanging-place-names-may-soon-be-punishable-in-manipur-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Bill%20that%20proposes%20this%20will%20likely%20be%20tabled%20in%20the%20upcoming%20Manipur%20assembly%20session.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fchanging-place-names-may-soon-be-punishable-in-manipur-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20millennials%20could%20give%20the%20suburbs%20a%20much-needed%20makeover%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Modern%20row%20houses%20in%20the%20suburbs%20of%20Delaware.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c3b5437a3d2714887890d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22719%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EModern%20row%20houses%20in%20the%20suburbs%20of%20Delaware.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Sohm%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20suburbs%20are%20home%20to%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20Americans%2C%20including%20millennials%20priced%20out%20of%20cities.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20car-centrism%20and%20separation%20of%20homes%20and%20commercial%20hubs%20exacerbate%20the%20worst%20of%20suburbia.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETo%20make%20suburbs%20healthier%20and%20more%20sustainable%2C%20urban%20experts%20say%20they%20should%20look%20more%20like%20towns.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20the%20American%20suburbs%20are%20seeing%20something%20of%20a%20revival%20after%20a%20few%20decades%20of%20the%20back-to-the-city%20movement%2C%C2%A0in%20which%20mostly%20young%20people%20flocked%20to%20urban%20centers.%20The%20rise%20of%20remote%20work%20coupled%20with%20the%20soaring%20costs%20of%20urban%20housing%20has%20pulled%2C%20or%20pushed%2C%20lots%20of%20millennials%20and%20others%20to%20the%20suburbs%20and%20even%20far-flung%20exurbs.%20Regardless%20of%20whether%20younger%20Americans%20prefer%20to%20settle%20and%20raise%20families%20in%20the%20suburbs%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-priced-out-of-cities-into-suburbs-housing-crisis-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eall%20they%20can%20afford%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fportal%2Fpdredge%2Fpdr-edge-frm-asst-sec-080320.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMost%20people%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20suburbanites%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20that%20likely%20won%E2%80%99t%20change%20anytime%20soon.%20Ideally%2C%20the%20suburbs%20offer%20the%20best%20of%20both%20the%20urban%20and%20rural%20worlds%3A%20a%20white%20picket%20fence%20within%20reach%20of%20downtown%20jobs%20and%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20sprawl%20has%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinherent%20geometry%20problem%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Andrew%20Justus%2C%20a%20housing-policy%20analyst%20at%20the%20Niskanen%20Center%2C%20a%20nonpartisan%20think%20tank.%20As%20a%20suburb%20or%20exurb%20grows%20to%20accommodate%20more%20homes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20are%20mostly%20limited%20to%20detached%20single-family%20houses%20%E2%80%94%20roads%20grow%2C%20cars%20multiply%2C%20and%20the%20distance%20between%20someone%E2%80%99s%20house%20and%20their%20job%2C%20school%2C%20or%20grocery%20store%20stretches.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20end%20up%20with%20suburbs%20that%20are%20neither%20close%20to%20the%20outskirts%20nor%20close%20to%20the%20city%20center%E2%80%9D%20and%20residents%20are%20%E2%80%9Ctrapped%20between%E2%80%9D%20the%20two%20worlds%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justus%20said.%20This%20is%20how%20suburbs%20got%20their%20bad%20reputation%20as%20isolating%2C%20boring%2C%20and%20unsustainable.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20for%20urbanists%2C%20housing%20advocates%2C%20and%20anyone%20who%20cares%20about%20climate%20change%20is%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20make%20the%20communities%20most%20Americans%20live%20in%20healthier%20for%20their%20inhabitants%20and%20the%20planet.%20This%20is%20where%20a%20kind%20of%20decentralized%20urbanism%20comes%20in.%20Experts%20say%20the%20solution%20is%20to%20make%20suburbs%20denser%2C%20more%20walkable%2C%20and%20more%20mixed-use%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0essentially%20more%20like%20traditional%20towns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20got%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20meet%20people%20where%20they%20live%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Adie%20Tomer%2C%20an%20expert%20in%20infrastructure%20policy%20and%20urban%20economics%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EExclusive%2C%20isolating%2C%20and%20inconvenient%20suburbs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20suburbs%20have%20always%20been%20flawed%20in%20a%20host%20of%20ways.%20Beginning%20in%20the%20mid-19th%20century%2C%20new%20suburbs%20helped%20white%20families%20build%20wealth%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Ftrend-1-separate-and-unequal-neighborhoods-are-sustaining-racial-and-economic-injustice-in-the-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eenforcing%20racial%20segregation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20civil%20rights%20movement%20of%20the%201960s%20and%2070s%20and%20the%20early%20years%20of%20integration%2C%20suburbs%20facilitated%20white%20flight.%20While%20many%20more%20people%20of%20color%20live%20outside%20cities%20today%2C%20they%20largely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Ftrump-is-clinging-to-an-outdated-vision-of-americas-suburbs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edon%E2%80%99t%20live%20in%20the%20same%20suburban%20communities%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20white%20people.%20Racial%20segregation%20used%20to%20be%20enforced%20explicitly%20by%20the%20law.%C2%A0Now%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnextcity.org%2Furbanist-news%2Fapartheid-by-another-name-how-zoning-regulations-perpetuate-segregation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eperpetuated%20by%20policies%20like%20single-family%20zoning%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20illegal%20to%20build%20more%20affordable%20multi-family%20housing%20in%20most%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20restrictive%20zoning%20is%20also%20what%20separates%20homes%20from%20everything%20else%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0making%20it%20illegal%20to%20put%20amenities%20like%20grocery%20stores%2C%20pharmacies%2C%20and%20restaurants%20in%20a%20residential%20neighborhood.%20Car-centric%20design%20is%20isolating%2C%20particularly%20for%20kids%2C%20the%20elderly%2C%20and%20anyone%20else%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20drive.%20And%20an%20overreliance%20on%20cars%20has%20made%20vehicles%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbo.gov%2Fpublication%2F58861%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20top%20emitter%20of%20greenhouse%20gasses%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20for%20the%20last%20several%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20American%20traveled%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bts.gov%2Fstatistical-products%2Fsurveys%2Fnational-household-travel-survey-daily-travel-quick-facts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etwice%20as%20many%20miles%20in%202017%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20they%20did%20in%201969.%20The%20typical%20American%20lives%20seven%20miles%20from%20their%20local%20commercial%20hub.%20And%20just%2014%25%20of%20errands%20the%20median%20US%20resident%20makes%20are%20within%20a%2015-minute%20walk%20of%20where%20they%20live%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D959b27c8a83b66fc56e22b8df1a0641316fb436efae9121b50f66b9e09b96850%26postID%3D65c3b35dee61557013fb3b8b%26postSlug%3Dsuburbs-millennials-walkable-towns-cities-housing-affordability-loneliness-2024-2%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41562-023-01770-y%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20recent%20study%20by%20MIT%20researchers%20found%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20exchange%20for%20individual%20land%20ownership%20at%20a%20historic%20scale%2C%20American%20suburbanites%20sacrifice%20key%20freedoms%2C%20including%20the%20freedom%20of%20movement%2C%20and%20the%20loss%20of%20our%20most%20valuable%20asset%3A%20time%2C%20Tomer%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20view%20of%20County%20courthouse%20and%20Clocktower%20in%20the%20historic%20small%20town%20of%20Paoli%2C%20Indiana.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c3b5e67a3d271488789158%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22719%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAerial%20view%20of%20the%20county%20courthouse%20and%20clocktower%20in%20the%20historic%20small%20town%20of%20Paoli%2C%20Indiana.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Sohm%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20freedom%20of%20the%20small%20town%20or%20%E2%80%9815-minute%20city%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%9C15-minute%20city%E2%80%9D%20is%20perhaps%20the%20buzziest%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20and%20most%20controversial%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0urban%20planning%20concept%20right%20now.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20ensure%20people%20can%20work%2C%20shop%2C%20and%20play%20within%20a%2015-minute%20walk%2C%20bike%2C%20or%20transit%20ride%20from%20where%20they%20live.%20But%20many%20conservatives%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-03-02%2Fhow-did-the-15-minute-city-get-tangled-up-in-a-far-right-conspiracy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edenounced%20it%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20socialist%20plan%20to%20strip%20people%20of%20their%20freedom%20and%20cars.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2015-minute%20cities%20aren%E2%80%99t%20new.%20They%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fa6f50b7c-f78f-469d-b3f2-c6f505edaa9c%3FaccessToken%3DzwAGCYwxPdhAkdOm9Qt8949GndOz8sb1Be2qnA.MEUCIQD-XoGUepLQ4s62PWEmDUGH8PCOndgUggaOlkIVAwtV4gIgYcoFGfY-grW59442ity5GNHT3AsL5FxgHbNCgZGGn_o%26sharetype%3Dgift%26token%3D17bcc7f1-3b6b-420f-b72b-7ffcb035b30d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enaturally%20form%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20cities%20that%20allow%20for%20dense%2C%20mixed-use%20development%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20they%20existed%20in%20America%E2%80%99s%20early%20suburbs%2C%20which%20were%20built%20around%20streetcars%2C%20rather%20than%20private%20vehicles.%20Because%20streetcars%20required%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20residential%20density%20to%20have%20sufficient%20ridership%2C%20those%20suburbs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0places%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnu.org%2Fpublicsquare%2Fcity-returns-its-streetcar-roots%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESomerville%2C%20Massachusetts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shakersquare.net%2Fhistory%2Fbefore-rapid.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShaker%20Heights%2C%20Ohio%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20much%20more%20like%20small%20cities%20or%20large%20towns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20progressive%20and%20conservative%20urban%20experts%20can%20agree%20on%20one%20thing%3A%20the%20suburbs%20need%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoel%20Kotkin%2C%20a%20fellow%20in%20urban%20studies%20at%20Chapman%20University%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalreview.com%2F2024%2F01%2Flet-america-sprawl%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erecently%20expounded%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20virtues%20of%20sprawl%20in%20the%20conservative%20National%20Review%2C%20wants%20to%20see%20the%20country%20turn%20into%20an%20archipelago%20of%20villages%20or%20towns.%20He%20points%20to%20suburbs%20like%20Orange%2C%20California%2C%20Bronxville%20in%20Westchester%20County%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.visitthewoodlands.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Woodlands%20in%20Texas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20master-planned%20suburb%20of%20Houston%20founded%20in%20the%201970s.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKotkin%20says%20the%20American%20suburbs%20have%20%E2%80%9Cwon%20the%20battle%E2%80%9D%20with%20cities%2C%20reigning%20as%20the%20more%20economically%20and%20demographically%20dominant%20place.%20But%20%E2%80%9Cwhat%20they%20haven't%20done%20is%20adjusted%20to%20that%20role%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20Suburbs%20need%20to%20reinvent%20themselves%20to%20look%20more%20like%20towns%20or%20small%20cities%20to%20better%20%E2%80%9Csatisfy%20the%20urban%20appetites%20of%20their%20new%20residents%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetrofitting%20suburbs%20to%20look%20more%20like%20towns%20%E2%80%9Cis%20the%20opportunity%20to%20not%20have%20your%20cake%20and%20eat%20it%20too%20but%20about%20as%20close%20as%20you%20can%20get%20to%20it%20in%20an%20American%20context%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tomer%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProgressives%20agree.%20%E2%80%9CA%20lot%20of%20people%20think%20we're%20trying%20to%20limit%20freedom%20by%20saying%20that%20we%20should%20have%20more%20public%20transit%20and%20maybe%20fewer%20car-centric%20developments%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Tayana%20Panova%2C%20an%20urban%20researcher%20writing%20a%20book%20about%20suburbia's%20effects%20on%20mental%20health.%20%E2%80%9CNo%2C%20we're%20trying%20to%20give%20you%20more%20freedom%20by%20giving%20you%20more%20options.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUrban%20planners%20say%20closer-in%2C%20streetcar%20suburbs%20with%20established%20downtowns%20are%20the%20easiest%20to%20transform%20into%20dense%2C%20walkable%20communities.%20But%20all%20kinds%20of%20suburbs%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20free%20themselves%20from%20traffic%20and%20long%20commutes%20and%20create%20more%20vibrant%20neighborhoods.%20Suburbs%20need%20to%20prioritize%20loosening%20zoning%20laws%2C%20building%20more%20dense%20housing%2C%20and%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20get%20places%20without%20a%20car%2C%20experts%20say.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere's%20a%20core%20principle%2C%20which%20is%20start%20small%20and%20use%20the%20assets%20you've%20already%20got%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tomer%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20he%20says%2C%20take%20an%20underused%20shopping%20center%20and%20put%20a%20market%20hall%20in%20it%2C%20build%20some%20multi-family%20housing%20nearby%2C%20and%20make%20the%20roads%20safer%20for%20pedestrians%20and%20bicyclists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETomer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fbuilding-for-proximity-the-role-of-activity-centers-in-reducing-total-miles-traveled%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efound%20in%20his%20recent%20study%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9CBuilding%20for%20Proximity%2C%E2%80%9D%20that%20people%20in%20the%20110%20largest%20US%20metros%20who%20live%20within%20three%20miles%20of%20so-called%20%E2%80%9Cactivity%20centers%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0recreation%20and%20shopping%20hubs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0drive%20much%20less%20than%20their%20more%20far-flung%20counterparts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20want%20to%20live%20in%20these%20types%20of%20neighborhoods.%20An%20analysis%20published%20last%20year%20found%20that%20homebuyers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartgrowthamerica.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FFoot-Traffic-Ahead-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ein%20the%2035%20biggest%20American%20metropolitan%20areas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20paid%2034%25%20more%20to%20live%20in%20walkable%20neighborhoods%2C%20while%20renters%20paid%2041%25%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20people%20are%20wanting%20these%20days%20is%20walkability%2C%E2%80%9D%20Panova%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20developers%2C%20if%20local%20governments%20and%20businesses%20are%20wise%20and%20are%20looking%20at%20the%20trends%20and%20what%20people%20are%20wanting%2C%20then%20they'll%20adapt%20to%20that.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20places%2C%20this%20is%20already%20happening.%20A%20surge%20of%20millennial%20transplants%20are%20bringing%20their%20urban%20sensibilities%20to%20the%20city%20outskirts.%20Suburban%20retail%20is%20booming%20%E2%80%94%20half%20of%20Sweetgreen%20salad%20shops%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fthe-decline-of-the-five-day-commute-is-a-boon-to-suburban-retail-55e4dc89%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eare%20now%20in%20the%20suburbs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20up%20from%2035%25%20four%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20so%20many%20towns%20that%20in%20the%20last%20five%2C%20six%20years%20I've%20seen%20huge%20revitalizations%2C%20where%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20restaurants%20and%20exercise%20studios%20and%20trendy%20stores%20start%20to%20pop%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Allison%20Levine%2C%20director%20of%20communications%20for%20the%20Suburban%20Jungle%20Group%2C%20a%20real-estate%20advisory%20firm%20that%20specializes%20in%20helping%20New%20York%20City%20dwellers%20move%20to%20surrounding%20suburbs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-priced-out-of-cities-into-suburbs-housing-crisis-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etold%20Business%20Insider%20in%20January%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20move%20to%20the%20suburbs%20and%20not%20feel%20like%20you%20need%20to%20go%20to%20the%20city%20to%20have%20a%20great%20dinner%20or%20to%20see%20a%20show%20or%20live%20music%20or%20the%20arts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuburbs-millennials-walkable-towns-cities-housing-affordability-loneliness-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707650581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c3b5f37a3d271488789168%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuburbs-millennials-walkable-towns-cities-housing-affordability-loneliness-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20American%20suburbs%20can%20be%20isolating%2C%20boring%2C%20and%20unsustainable%20places.%20Bike%20lanes%2C%20apartment%20buildings%2C%20and%20Sweetgreen%20could%20fix%20that.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuburbs-millennials-walkable-towns-cities-housing-affordability-loneliness-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Boeing%20lost%20its%20way.%20Other%20companies%20should%20take%20heed.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221778%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20illustration%20of%20Boeing%20planes.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c262e17a3d271488782672%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBoeing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20entire%20American%20corporate%20body%20politic%20%E2%80%94%20needs%20a%20philosophical%20counterrevolution.%C2%A0%3Cp%3ECameron%20Spencer%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20only%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20problems%20were%20just%20about%20a%20nightmare%20flight%20%E2%80%94%20a%20screw%20loose%2C%20a%20blown-out%20door%20plug%2C%20and%20177%20people%20who%20will%20probably%20need%20therapy%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20lives.%20But%20as%20the%20iconic%20American%20plane%20manufacturer%20tries%20to%20make%20amends%20for%20the%20disastrous%20Alaska%20Airlines%20flight%20in%20January%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20become%20clear%20that%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20problems%20run%20far%20deeper.%20They%20expose%20decades%20of%20American%20corporate%20philosophy%20gone%20awry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoeing%20is%20a%20quintessential%20example%20of%20America%E2%80%99s%20rotting%20business%20culture%20over%20the%20past%2040%20years.%20The%20company%20relentlessly%20disgorged%20cash%20to%20shareholders%20when%20it%20could%E2%80%99ve%20spent%20it%20on%20building%20a%20better%20(and%20safer)%20product.%20Investments%20that%20could%E2%80%99ve%20benefited%20employees%2C%20communities%2C%20and%20other%20corporate%20stakeholders%20were%20often%20sacrificed%20at%20the%20altar%20of%20efficiency%20and%20free%20cash%20flow.%20Boeing%20focused%20on%20pleasing%20Wall%20Street%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20American%20executives%20believe%20companies%20should%20operate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20people%20who%20are%20at%20the%20top%20are%20there%20for%20a%20reason%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20basically%20to%20maximize%20shareholder%20value%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20University%20of%20Massachusetts%20economist%20William%20Lazonick%20told%20me.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20so%20ingrained%20in%20their%20thinking%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20the%20problem%20itself.%20It%E2%80%99s%20built%20into%20the%20structure%20of%20these%20companies.%E2%80%9DSimply%20changing%20CEOs%20or%20hiring%20more%20engineers%20won%E2%80%99t%20make%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20problems%20go%20away.%20The%20company%20needs%20to%20rethink%20its%20very%20reason%20for%20existing%20and%20what%20it%20should%20provide%20to%20society%20as%20an%20enterprise.%20A%20good%20American%20company%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20a%20vehicle%20for%20financial%20returns%3B%20it%20is%20first%20and%20foremost%20an%20employer%2C%20a%20contributor%20to%20economic%20and%2For%20technological%20innovation%2C%20and%20a%20source%20of%20US%20power.%20Whether%20the%20recent%20disasters%20shake%20Boeing%20out%20of%20its%20somnambulance%20remains%20unclear.%20It%E2%80%99s%20also%20questionable%20whether%20other%20major%20companies%20with%20a%20similar%20maximize-shareholder-value-at-all-costs%20ethos%20will%20learn%20from%20the%20mistakes.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20clear%20that%20what%20Boeing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20entire%20American%20corporate%20body%20politic%20%E2%80%94%20needs%20is%20nothing%20short%20of%20a%20philosophical%20counterrevolution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%20a%20time%20when%20pilots%20had%20stickers%20on%20their%20bags%20that%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20it%20ain%E2%80%99t%20Boeing%2C%20I%20ain%E2%80%99t%20going.%E2%80%9D%20Founded%20in%201916%2C%20the%20manufacturer%20helped%20the%20US%20launch%20NASA%20and%20win%20World%20War%20II.%20For%20decades%20it%20was%20the%20pinnacle%20of%20American%20engineering.%20%E2%80%9CBoeing%20was%20America%E2%80%99s%20crown%20jewel%2C%E2%80%9D%20William%20McGee%2C%20a%20journalist%2C%20advocate%2C%20and%20aviation-industry%20old%20hand%2C%20told%20me.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20and%20impressive%20companies%20in%20the%20US.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20started%20to%20change%20in%20the%20late%201980s%20when%20T.A.%20Wilson%2C%20the%20last%20Boeing%20CEO%20with%20an%20engineering%20background%2C%20was%20replaced%20by%20Frank%20Shrontz%2C%20an%20attorney%20and%20businessman.%20The%20choice%20was%20a%20signal%20to%20Wall%20Street%20that%20engineering%20excesses%20would%20be%20curbed%20in%20favor%20of%20cost%20discipline%20and%20investor%20rewards.%20Lazonick%E2%80%99s%20research%20indicates%20that%20from%201998%20to%202018%2C%20Boeing%20did%20%2461%20billion%20worth%20of%20share%20buybacks%20to%20pump%20its%20stock%20price%20and%20paid%20out%20%2429.3%20billion%20in%20dividends.%20Over%20these%20three%20decades%20of%20plenty%20for%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20shareholders%2C%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20staff%20was%20asked%20to%20penny-pinch.%20An%20investigation%20into%20battery%20fires%20on%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20787%20Dreamliner%20in%202013%20found%20that%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20allowing%20engineers%20to%20stress%20test%20its%20products%20enough%2C%20that%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20catching%20manufacturing%20defects%2C%20and%20that%20passengers%20could%20be%20in%20danger%20as%20a%20result.%20But%20he%20finance%20guys%20loved%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20new%20focus%2C%20and%20the%20C-suite%20%E2%80%94%20which%20receives%20the%20lion's%20share%20of%20its%20compensation%20in%20stock%20%E2%80%94%20loved%20it%20too.%20In%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202019%2C%20Boeing%20announced%20a%20%242.7%20billion%20stock%20buyback%2C%20and%20the%20market%20rewarded%20the%20company%20with%20an%20all-time-high%20share%20price%20of%20%24426.76.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20later%20that%20year%2C%20it%20all%20fell%20apart.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20737%20Max%208%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20the%20most%20efficient%2C%20cost-effective%2C%20environmentally%20friendly%20regional%20shuttle%20aircraft%20on%20the%20market.%20Instead%2C%20the%20plane%20exposed%20the%20rot%20at%20the%20core%20of%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20culture.%20In%20his%20book%20%E2%80%9CFlying%20Blind%3A%20The%20737%20Max%20Tragedy%20and%20the%20Fall%20of%20Boeing%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20journalist%20Peter%20Robison%20wrote%20that%20when%20the%20new%20model%20was%20being%20built%2C%20managers%20asked%20for%20a%20detailed%20accounting%20of%20every%20test%20flight%20and%20talked%20frequently%20about%20how%20any%20change%20had%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbuy%20its%20way%20onto%20the%20airplane.%E2%80%9D%20A%20manager%20lamented%20to%20one%20of%20Robison%E2%80%99s%20sources%20that%20people%20would%20%E2%80%9Chave%20to%20die%E2%80%9D%20before%20Boeing%20made%20changes%20to%20the%20aircraft.%20And%20so%20they%20did%3A%20Two%20crashes%20%E2%80%94%20which%20were%20the%20result%20of%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20work%20around%20a%20technical%20failure%20%E2%80%94%20claimed%20the%20lives%20of%20more%20than%20300%20people%20and%20grounded%20the%20737%20Max%208%20for%20nine%20months.%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20stock%20cratered%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbus-set-to-break-order-records-beat-boeing-fifth-year-in-a-row-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EFrance%E2%80%99s%20Airbus%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20rival%20once%20colloquially%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9CScare%20Bus%2C%E2%80%9D%20started%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbus-struggling-outsider-beating-boeing-737-max-a320neo-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Eeat%20the%20American%20company%E2%80%99s%20lunch%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExecutives%20promised%20to%20fix%20the%20problems%20that%20plagued%20the%20737%20Max%208%2C%20but%20the%20recent%20Alaska%20Airlines%20Max%209%20mess%20has%20returned%20the%20focus%20to%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20communication%2C%20supply%20chain%2C%20and%20overall%20quality-control%20failures.%20In%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20quarterly%20earnings%20call%20at%20the%20end%20of%20January%2C%20President%20and%20CEO%20Dave%20Calhoun%20(who%20was%20hired%20after%20the%20previous%20737%20Max%20disaster)%20promised%20more%20of%20a%20focus%20on%20quality%20and%20encouraged%20employees%20to%20speak%20up%20about%20issues%20on%20the%20factory%20floor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20day%20one%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20been%20focused%20on%20inculcating%20safety%20and%20quality%20to%20everything%20that%20we%20do%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cand%20getting%20back%20to%20our%20legacy%20of%20getting%20engineering%20excellence%20back%20at%20the%20center%20of%20our%20business.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20many%20talking-head%20Wall%20Street%20analysts%20and%20TV%20stock%20influencers%2C%20Calhoun%E2%80%99s%20comments%20were%20enough.%20Sure%2C%20this%20is%20a%20rough%20period%20for%20the%20company%2C%20but%20Boeing%20would%20be%20fine.%20Buy%20the%20dip.%20Others%20in%20the%20aviation%20industry%20aren%E2%80%99t%20so%20sure.%20United%20Airlines%20CEO%20Scott%20Kirby%2C%20one%20of%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20customers%2C%20called%20the%20Max%209%20fiasco%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20straw%20that%20broke%20the%20camel%E2%80%99s%20back.%E2%80%9D%20He%20expressed%20frustration%20at%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20seemingly%20constant%20blunders%20and%20its%20nearly%20five-year%20delay%20in%20the%20delivery%20of%20the%20Max%2010%20(which%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20certified%20by%20the%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration).%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20at%20least%20build%20a%20plan%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20Max%2010%20in%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20CNBC.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERather%20than%20a%20blip%20on%20the%20radar%2C%20this%20should%20be%20a%20come-to-Jesus%20moment%20for%20Boeing%20%E2%80%94%20a%20moment%20when%20it%20puts%20engineering%20back%20at%20the%20center%20of%20its%20culture.%20Some%20have%20argued%20that%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20problems%20go%20back%20further%20and%20are%20bigger%20than%20the%20recent%20quality%20issues.%20But%20the%20problems%20are%20the%20result%20of%20something%20even%20bigger%20than%20Boeing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20transition%20from%20an%20obsession%20with%20engineering%20to%20an%20obsession%20with%20financial%20engineering%20at%20Boeing%2C%20Lazonick%20told%20me%2C%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20the%20case%20of%20one%20company%20suddenly%20changing%20strategy%3B%20it%20%E2%80%9Creflected%20what%20was%20going%20on%20in%20the%20US.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUntil%20the%201970s%2C%20he%20says%2C%20corporations%20were%20generally%20considered%20parts%20of%20a%20community%20with%20responsibilities%20to%20a%20plethora%20of%20stakeholders%3A%20the%20employees%20who%20work%20for%20them%2C%20the%20communities%20that%20house%20them%2C%20the%20customers%20who%20pay%20for%20their%20products.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20then%20the%20US%20stock%20market%20flatlined%2C%20and%20the%20economy%20was%20in%20the%20doldrums%2C%20so%20Wall%20Street%20and%20Washington%20decided%20that%20the%20way%20American%20companies%20did%20business%20needed%20a%20shake-up.%20This%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20simple%20tweak%20around%20the%20edges%20%E2%80%94%20refining%20regulations%20and%20adding%20a%20few%20new%20roles%20to%20executive%20teams%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20about%20an%20ideological%20full-court%20press%20to%20change%20American%20corporate%20culture.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20root%20of%20this%20shake-up%20was%20the%20influence%20of%20the%20economist%20Milton%20Friedman%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago.%20In%20Friedman%E2%80%99s%20view%2C%20humans%20are%20selfish%20and%20look%20out%20for%20their%20own%20interests%20by%20nature.%20He%20argued%20that%20meant%20a%20company%20would%20see%20its%20social%20responsibility%20as%20being%20to%20its%20shareholders%20and%20its%20shareholders%20alone.%20One%20of%20Friedman%E2%80%99s%20disciples%2C%20the%20economist%20Michael%20Jensen%2C%20took%20the%20theory%20a%20step%20further%20in%201976%20and%20argued%20that%20the%20corporation%20should%20be%20built%20to%20serve%20the%20interests%20of%20shareholders.%20Soon%20the%20two%20economists%E2%80%99%20ideas%20were%20finding%20acolytes%20at%20business%20schools%2C%20think%20tanks%2C%20and%20congressional%20offices%20around%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJensen%20in%20particular%20pushed%20for%20CEOs%20to%20be%20paid%20in%20stock%2C%20arguing%20that%20they%20were%20being%20paid%20like%20bureaucrats%20and%20needed%20their%20compensation%20to%20be%20more%20in%20line%20with%20performance.%20This%20incentivized%20CEOs%20to%20maximize%20profits%20for%20shareholders.%20It%E2%80%99s%20probably%20no%20surprise%20that%20CEO%20pay%20increased%20by%201%2C322%25%20from%201978%20to%202020.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ideas%20also%20started%20to%20permeate%20Washington.%20Rule%20changes%20had%20allowed%20companies%20to%20repurchase%20their%20own%20shares%2C%20a%20practice%20that%20was%20previously%20considered%20stock%20manipulation%20and%20a%20general%20waste%20of%20capital%20that%20should%20be%20reinvested%20in%20the%20company.%20It%20also%20opened%20the%20door%20for%20Wall%20Street%E2%80%99s%20corporate%20raiders%20to%20pressure%20management%20to%20buy%20back%20stock%20to%20juice%20the%20price.%20Money%20that%20could%20have%20been%20spent%20investing%20in%20workers%20or%20products%20instead%20went%20straight%20to%20investors.%20By%20the%201990s%2C%20nary%20a%20thought%20was%20given%20to%20whether%20efficiency%20was%20enough%20of%20a%20reason%20to%20send%20jobs%20overseas.%20There%20was%20no%20time%20for%20that%20while%20politicians%20were%20busy%20talking%20about%20how%20America%20should%20be%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fmagazine%2Farchive%2F2002%2F10%2Fthe-roaring-nineties%2F302604%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Erun%20as%20a%20business%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CEO%20who%20best%20personified%20this%20ideology%20was%20Jack%20Welch%2C%20who%20helmed%20General%20Electric%20from%201981%20to%202001.%20During%20his%20tenure%2C%20he%20was%20celebrated%20as%20one%20of%20America%E2%80%99s%20great%20CEOs%20for%20putting%20shareholder%20primacy%20into%20practice.%20He%20sliced%20costs%20for%20the%20things%20that%20had%20made%20the%20company%20innovative%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20like%20research%2C%20development%2C%20and%20quality%20control%20%E2%80%94%20and%20siphoned%20them%20off%20to%20shareholders%20in%20the%20form%20of%20buybacks%20and%20dividend%20payments.%20Wall%20Street%20rewarded%20his%20mentality%20richly%2C%20GE%E2%80%99s%20stock%20peaked%20at%20%24318.26%20in%202000%2C%20and%20Welch%E2%80%99s%20disciples%20at%20GE%20spread%20out%20all%20over%20corporate%20America.%20But%20a%20corporation%20can%20run%20on%20past%20innovation%20only%20for%20so%20long.%20In%202018%2C%20after%20over%20100%20years%20of%20prestige%2C%20GE%20was%20dropped%20from%20the%20Dow%20Jones%20Industrial%20Average%20because%20of%20the%20work%20Welch%20did%20to%20hollow%20it%20out.%20During%20the%20first%20few%20years%20of%20his%20tenure%20he%20fired%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20company%20and%20continued%20to%20fire%2010%25%20of%20the%20workforce%20annually%20thereafter.%20He%20was%20such%20a%20fan%20of%20sending%20factories%20abroad%20%E2%80%94%20to%20American%20unions%E2%80%99%20ire%20%E2%80%94%20that%20he%20infamously%20said%2C%20''Ideally%2C%20you'd%20have%20every%20plant%20you%20own%20on%20a%20barge.''%20GE%20was%20stripped%20to%20free%20up%20cash%20for%20shareholders%20time%20and%20time%20again%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20those%2C%20of%20course%2C%20being%20Welch.%20Even%20after%20he%20left%20the%20company%2C%20his%20pay%20package%20was%20so%20avaricious%20that%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20fined%20GE%20in%202004%20for%20failing%20to%20disclose%20its%20magnitude.%20The%20problem%20with%20playing%20Wall%20Street%E2%80%99s%20game%20is%20that%20you%20have%20to%20keep%20playing%20forever%2C%20and%20the%20efficiency%20doctrine%20has%20diminishing%20returns.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ones%20where%20the%20most%20value%20is%20being%20extracted%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20were%20the%20most%20innovative%20in%20the%20past%2C%E2%80%9D%20Lazonick%20told%20me%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20then%20they%20go%20into%20decline.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-baby-boomers-became-the-most-selfish-generation-2016-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20entire%20generation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20politicians%20and%20executives%20preached%20the%20doctrine%20of%20efficiency%20in%20the%20name%20of%20maximizing%20profits%20for%20shareholders%2C%20and%20we%E2%80%99ve%20seen%20the%20results%3A%20stagnant%20wages%2C%20massive%20inequality%2C%20legislators%20captured%20by%20industry%20lobbyists%2C%20and%20companies%20that%20coast%20on%20past%20innovation%20and%20financialization%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20easier%20than%20investing%20in%20something%20new.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Boeing%20has%20been%20forced%20to%20reckon%20with%20the%20corporate%20culture%20it%20developed%20over%20the%20past%2040%20years%2C%20corporate%20America%20has%20been%20forced%20to%20face%20the%20long-term%20cost%20of%20its%20obsession%20with%20shareholder%20primacy%20and%20efficiency.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20lost%20a%20sense%20of%20balancing%20stakeholder%20interests.%20Not%20every%20company%20is%20as%20rich%20as%2C%20for%20example%2C%20Meta%2C%20which%20has%20been%20able%20to%20invest%20%2450%20billion%20in%20Reality%20Labs%20(the%20%E2%80%9Cmetaverse%E2%80%9D)%20since%202020%20and%20still%20buy%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-zuckerberg-dividend-stock-buyback-growth-shareholder-returns-buffett-berkshire-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Eback%20its%20own%20stock%20at%20its%20highs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Deutsche%20Bank%20has%20projected%20that%20across%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20buybacks%20will%20surge%20to%20%241%20trillion%20in%202024.%20Surely%20not%20all%20of%20these%20companies%20occupy%20the%20same%20reality%20%E2%80%94%20virtual%2C%20financial%2C%20or%20otherwise.%20Besides%2C%20part%20of%20Wall%20Street%E2%80%99s%20good%20vibes%20for%20Meta%20stem%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20company%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-office-closures-stock-price-mark-zuckerberg-earnings-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Ecut%2022%25%20of%20its%20workforce%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20In%20an%20economy%20where%20taxpayers%20kept%20some%20businesses%20afloat%20through%20the%20pandemic%2C%20widespread%20layoffs%20in%20the%20name%20of%20efficiency%20and%20shareholder%20value%20will%20hit%20a%20nerve%20that%20has%20been%20irritated%20for%20years%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmericans%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20they%E2%80%99re%20shareholders%20are%20not%20%E2%80%94%20have%20started%20to%20notice%20their%20contributions%20to%20the%20corporations%20as%20workers%20and%20taxpayers%20are%20being%20taken%20for%20granted%2C%20and%20they%E2%80%99re%20naturally%20angry.%20The%20populism%20that%20has%20taken%20over%20our%20political%20discourse%20is%20anger%20over%20inequality%20harnessed%20for%20political%20action.%20In%20response%2C%20executives%20have%20offered%20only%20lip%20service.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20Business%20Roundtable%2C%20an%20advocacy%20group%20formed%20in%20the%201970s%20for%20corporations%2C%20read%20the%20populist%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fhow-short-termism-saps-the-economy-1475018087%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Etea%20leaves%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20published%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessroundtable.org%2Fbusiness-roundtable-redefines-the-purpose-of-a-corporation-to-promote-an-economy-that-serves-all-americans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Estatement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20said%20the%20purpose%20of%20a%20corporation%20was%20to%20serve%20all%20stakeholders%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopportunity.businessroundtable.org%2Fourcommitment%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Ecustomers%2C%20employees%2C%20suppliers%2C%20communities%20and%20shareholders%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20problem%20is%20it%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20see%20how%20corporate%20behavior%20has%20actually%20changed%20since%20then.%20Look%20at%20General%20Motors.%20Right%20now%2C%20the%20company%20is%20trying%20to%20keep%20up%20in%20a%20global%20race%20to%20electrify%20the%20car%20industry.%20If%20there%20was%20any%20time%20to%20focus%20on%20productive%20investments%20over%20shareholders%E2%80%99%20wallets%2C%20this%20would%20be%20it.%20When%20the%20United%20Auto%20Workers%20union%20went%20on%20strike%20in%20September%2C%20CEO%20Mary%20Barra%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ineteconomics.org%2Fperspectives%2Fblog%2Fhow-gms-10-billion-buyback-may-ice-its-ev-transition%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Ewarned%20workers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20it%20would%20cost%20the%20company%20money%20that%20should%20be%20invested%20in%20that%20transition.%20But%20in%20November%2C%20after%20the%20strike%2C%20she%20announced%20a%20%2410%20billion%20stock%20buyback%2C%20the%20company's%20largest%20share-repurchase%20plan%20and%20a%20larger%20sum%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fautos-transportation%2Fgm-buy-back-10-billion-shares-cut-cruise-spending-2023-11-29%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Ethan%20it%20gave%20its%20workers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20size%20of%20the%20buybacks%20is%20even%20more%20staggering%20when%20you%20consider%20that%20the%20company%20promised%20to%20spend%20%2435%20billion%20total%20on%20developing%20EVs%20from%202020%20to%202025.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECompanies%20like%20GM%20and%20Boeing%20are%20crucial%20to%20the%20American%20economy.%20Their%20success%20keeps%20people%20employed%20and%20enriches%20communities%2C%20which%20is%20good%20for%20society.%20Maintaining%20and%20growing%20these%20iconic%20companies%20is%20a%20long-term%20business%2C%20but%20the%20people%20who%20run%20the%20business%20are%20motivated%20to%20play%20a%20short-term%20game.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBoeing%20is%20vital%2C%20but%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20treat%20it%20like%20it%E2%80%99s%20vital%2C%E2%80%9D%20McGee%20said.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20treat%20it%20like%20a%20casino.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20ways%20to%20change%20all%20of%20this%2C%20as%20Lazonick%20outlines%20in%20his%202023%20book%20%E2%80%9CInvesting%20in%20Innovation.%E2%80%9D%20Companies%20could%20decouple%20executive%20pay%20from%20stock%20prices%20or%20change%20the%20composition%20of%20boards%20to%20include%20employees.%20But%20more%20fundamentally%2C%20it%20will%20take%20a%20total%20rethink%20of%20America%E2%80%99s%20corporate%20incentive%20structure.%20Instead%20of%20favoring%20shareholders%20and%20playing%20a%20quarterly%20game%20with%20Wall%20Street%2C%20C-suites%20should%20prioritize%20sustainable%2C%20long-term%20businesses%20that%20employ%20as%20many%20productive%20workers%20as%20possible.%20This%20means%20companies%20won%E2%80%99t%20suddenly%20fall%20out%20of%20the%20sky%20when%20the%20economy%20sours%20or%20their%20products%20start%20to%20give%20way%20for%20lack%20of%20investment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Boeing%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20that%20could%20mean%20bringing%20suppliers%20closer%20to%20home%2C%20investing%20in%20more%20layers%20of%20quality%20control%2C%20and%20allowing%20more%20time%20for%20testing%20and%20research.%20It%20could%20mean%20a%20more%20expensive%2C%20more%20redundant%20company%2C%20but%20a%20better%20one.%20The%20first%20step%20is%20believing%20that%20the%20state%20of%20Boeing%20is%20not%20a%20natural%20one%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it%20can%20be%20changed%20with%20conscious%20effort.%20We%20just%20have%20to%20choose%20a%20better%20way.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flinette-lopez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ELinette%20Lopez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-disaster-american-businesses-greedy-broken-stock-market-wall-street-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707650521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c262e17a3d271488782672%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-disaster-american-businesses-greedy-broken-stock-market-wall-street-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Boeing%20is%20a%20quintessential%20example%20of%20America's%20rotting%20business%20culture.