nsider.com%2F65c5358e43bb77284ba50fb4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EApple%3B%20Mike%20Kemp%2FIn%20Pictures%20via%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reviews%20are%20in%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-fans-react-to-the-apple-vision-pro-demo-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etech%20press%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20lauding%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-vision-pro-unboxing-what-comes-with-headset%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20Apple%20Vision%20Pro%20headset%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20delivering%20on%20the%20company's%20promises.%20It's%20well-designed%2C%20the%20video%20and%20sound%20are%20startlingly%20precise%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BMinority%20Report%26quot%3B-style%20gestural%20interface%20is%20future-tastic.%20Nobody's%20exactly%20sure%20what%20it's%20for%2C%20or%20whether%20even%20the%20Readiest%20Players%20One%20will%20spend%20%243%2C500%20on%20it%2C%20but%20hey%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20gadgets%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20this%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcant-afford-apple-vision-pro-five-alternative-headsets-meta-quest-2024-2%23x-reals-air-2-ultra-starting-from-699-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enew%20gadget%20frontier%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Vision%20Pro%2C%20like%20the%20similarly%20kitted-out%20Quest%203%20and%20Quest%20Pro%20headsets%20from%20Meta%2C%20uses%20what's%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bpassthrough%26quot%3B%20video%20%E2%80%94%20cameras%20and%20other%20sensors%20that%20capture%20imagery%20of%20the%20outside%20world%20and%20reproduce%20it%20inside%20the%20device.%20They%20feed%20you%20a%20synthetic%20environment%20made%20to%20look%20like%20the%20real%20one%2C%20with%20Apple%20apps%20and%20other%20non-real%20elements%20floating%20in%20front%20of%20it.%20Apple%20and%20Meta%20are%20hoping%20that%20this%20virtual%20world%20will%20be%20so%20compelling%20that%20you%20won't%20just%20visit.%20They're%20hoping%20you'll%20live%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20could%20have%20some%20very%20weird%20and%20very%20messy%20consequences%20for%20the%20human%20brain.%20Researchers%20have%20found%20that%20widespread%2C%20long-term%20immersion%20in%20VR%20headsets%20could%20literally%20change%20the%20way%20we%20perceive%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20and%20each%20other.%20%26quot%3BWe%20now%20have%20companies%20who%20are%20advocating%20that%20you%20spend%20many%20hours%20each%20day%20in%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jeremy%20Bailenson%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Virtual%20Human%20Interaction%20Lab%20at%20Stanford.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20many%2C%20many%20people%2C%20and%20they're%20wearing%20it%20for%20many%2C%20many%20hours.%20And%20everything%20magnifies%20at%20scale.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeaning%3A%20Our%20brains%20are%20about%20to%20undergo%20a%20massive%2C%20society-wide%20experiment%20that%20could%20rewire%20our%20sense%20of%20the%20world%20around%20us%2C%20and%20make%20it%20even%20harder%20to%20agree%20on%20what%20constitutes%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20short-term%20side%20effects%20of%20virtual%20reality%20are%20well%20established.%20People%20in%20synthetic%20environments%20tend%20to%20misjudge%20distance%2C%20both%20at%20a%20distance%20and%20close%20up.%20That's%20no%20surprise%3A%20Even%20in%20the%20real%2C%20three-dimensional%20universe%2C%20our%20ability%20to%20determine%20how%20close%20or%20far%20away%20something%20is%20is%20subject%20to%20all%20kinds%20of%20external%20factors.%20Virtual%20environments%2C%20with%20their%20lower%20resolution%20and%20synthetic%203D%2C%20make%20all%20that%20worse%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20especially%20bad%20if%20you're%20one%20of%20those%20users%20posting%20videos%20of%20yourself%20doing%20things%20like%20skateboarding%20and%20driving%20while%20wearing%20a%20mixed-reality%20headset.%20You%20think%20your%20hands%20are%20in%20one%20place%2C%20they're%20actually%20in%20another%2C%20and%20pretty%20soon%20you're%20driving%20your%20Honda%20Civic%20through%20a%20supermarket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObjects%20in%20a%20headset%20can%20also%20get%20funhoused.%20That's%20called%20object%20distortion%20%E2%80%94%20things%20get%20warped%2C%20and%20change%20size%20or%20shape%20or%20color%2C%20especially%20when%20you%20move%20your%20head.%20A%20video%20render%20can't%20compete%20with%20the%20processing%20speed%20and%20fidelity%20of%20your%20eyes%20and%20brain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221856%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Apple%20Vision%20Pro%20headset%20displaying%20apps%20overlayed%20in%20a%20user's%20living%20room.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647e289340bf000019fa3d18%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EApple%20Vision%20Pro%3Cp%3EApple%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20all%2C%20as%20the%20IT%20people%20say%2C%20known%20issues.%20For%20a%20few%20minutes%20or%20an%20hour%2C%20long%20enough%20to%20play%20a%20game%20or%20watch%20a%20movie%2C%20they're%20minor%20annoyances.%20But%20wear%20perception-shifting%20glasses%20for%20days%20at%20a%20time%20%E2%80%94%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvhil.stanford.edu%2Fpublications%2Fimmersionpresence%2Fseeing-world-through-digital-prisms-psychological-implications%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWe%2520conclude%2520that%2520the%2520passthrough%2Cand%2520interfere%2520with%2520social%2520connection.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBailenson's%20team%20of%20researchers%20did%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20problems%20get%20worse.%20%3Cem%3EWay%20%3C%2Fem%3Eworse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20wore%20Vision%20Pros%20and%20Quests%20around%20college%20campuses%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20weeks%2C%20trying%20to%20do%20all%20the%20things%20they%20would%20have%20done%20without%20them%20(with%20a%20minder%20nearby%20in%20case%20they%20tripped%20or%20walked%20into%20a%20wall).%20They%20experienced%20%26quot%3Bsimulator%20sickness%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20nausea%2C%20headaches%2C%20dizziness.%20That%20was%20weird%2C%20given%20how%20experienced%20they%20all%20were%20with%20headsets%20of%20all%20kinds.%20And%20they%20felt%20all%20the%20distance%20and%20distortion%20effects%3A%20thinking%20elevator%20buttons%20were%20farther%20from%20their%20fingers%2C%20or%20experiencing%20difficulty%20bringing%20food%20to%20their%20mouths.%20But%20as%20any%20of%20us%20would%2C%20they%20adapted%20%E2%80%94%20their%20brains%20and%20muscles%20learned%20to%20compensate%20for%20their%20new%20view%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20seems%20like%20a%20solution%2C%20but%20it%20ain't.%20When%20people%20adapt%20to%20a%20perceptual%20change%20for%20long%20enough%2C%20the%20real%20world%20starts%20to%20look%20wrong%20in%20the%20opposite%20direction.%20If%20you%20wore%20glasses%20that%20turned%20your%20vision%20upside%20down%2C%20let's%20say%2C%20you'd%20have%20to%20adapt%20again%20when%20the%20glasses%20came%20off.%20The%20longer%20you're%20inside%20a%20funhouse%20world%2C%20the%20longer%20the%20weird%20perceptual%20aftereffects%20last.%20So%20people%20who%20spend%20their%20workday%20inside%20a%20Vision%20Pro%20might%20go%20home%20at%20night%20with%20a%20miscalibrated%20targeting%20system%20and%20what%20feels%20like%20a%20shroom%20hangover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20where%20the%20passthrough%20video%20gets%20uniquely%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eimportant.%20Old-school%20cyberpunk%20envisioned%20virtual%20reality%20as%20an%20all-encompassing%20synthetic%20environment.%20New-school%20techies%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20proposed%20an%20augmented%20reality%20of%20digital%20pop-ups%20floating%20on%20see-through%20lenses%2C%20Google%20Glass-style.%20But%20both%20of%20those%20approaches%20have%20limits.%20Full%2C%20sense-isolating%20VR%20hasn't%20progressed%20much%20further%20than%20niche%20entertainment%2C%20while%20AR%20tends%20to%20make%20both%20its%20apps%20and%20the%20real%20world%20look%20bad.%20From%20a%20visual%20standpoint%2C%20passthrough%20is%20the%20least-worst%20solution%20%E2%80%94%20but%20its%20social%20consequences%20are%20scarier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20passthrough%20captures%20and%20then%20re-renders%20reality%2C%20it%20can%20have%20an%20unnerving%2C%20distancing%20effect%20over%20time.%20When%20Bailenson's%20colleagues%20actually%20tried%20to%20talk%20to%20people%2C%20the%20world%20turned%20into%20a%20giant%2C%20confusing%20Zoom.%20Video%20chats%2C%20as%20we've%20all%20experienced%2C%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flargest-zoom-conversation-database-science-interact-video-chat-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eplagued%20by%20delays%20in%20responses%20and%20missed%20social%20cues%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Conversations%20lose%20subtlety%2C%20but%20it's%20good%20enough%20for%20a%20meeting.%20But%20passthrough%20magnifies%20the%20effect%20%E2%80%94%20the%20people%20you%20talk%20to%20start%20to%20seem%20%3Cem%3Eunreal%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Up%20close%2C%20they%20look%20like%20avatars.%20Farther%20away%2C%20they%20become%20just%20part%20of%20the%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBailenson%20describes%20the%20feeling%20as%20one%20of%20social%20absence.%20Other%20people%20just%20aren't%20fully%20there.%20He%20doesn't%20put%20it%20this%20way%2C%20but%20I'll%20wave%20the%20warning%20flag%3A%20Long-term%20use%20of%20passthrough%20headsets%20could%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20think%20of%20other%20people%20as%20unhumans%20%E2%80%94%20non-player%20characters%20in%20a%20gamified%2C%20uncanny%20valley.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20all%20live%20in%20our%20own%20perceptual%20bubbles.%20Every%20person%20has%20slightly%20different%20sensory%20thresholds%20%E2%80%94%20we%20see%20colors%20a%20little%20bit%20differently%2C%20hear%20at%20different%20levels%20of%20acuity%2C%20are%20more%20or%20less%20sensitive%20to%20different%20odors.%20And%20we%20process%20all%20that%20with%20brains%20uniquely%20tuned%20first%20by%20our%20genes%2C%20and%20then%20by%20a%20lifetime%20of%20neural%20changes%2C%20of%20thinking%20and%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20general%2C%20we%20agree%20on%20some%20common%20ground.%20Even%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Da8a3c4d59998da52f84f509cf96e1da29ee5371c20d7d0d17d1738c7b9f26e16%26postID%3D65c15f182eedcd8f95e7f824%26postSlug%3Dapple-vision-pro-experiment-brain-virtual-reality-side-effect-2024-2%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FFull-Spectrum-Science-Color-Modern%252Fdp%252F1328518906%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eyour%20blue%20looks%20a%20little%20different%20than%20mine%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20can%20agree%20on%20what%20color%20the%20sky%20is.%20Maybe%20my%20tolerance%20for%20chili%20peppers%20is%20higher%20than%20yours%2C%20but%20we%20both%20know%20when%20we're%20eating%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeadsets%20make%20the%20walls%20of%20those%20sensory%20bubbles%20even%20thicker%2C%20and%20harder%20to%20bridge.%20We%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-twitter-facebook-political-polarization-mechanism-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elack%20for%20common%20ground%20politically%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Now%2C%20as%20millions%20of%20Americans%20wear%20VR%20headsets%20for%20hours%20at%20a%20time%2C%20we%20may%20find%20ourselves%20unable%20to%20agree%20on%20our%20%3Cem%3Ephysical%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereality.%20The%20headsets%20will%20put%20things%20into%20our%20visual%20world%20that%20aren't%20there%20for%20anyone%20else.%20The%20objects%20aren't%20objective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20not%20all.%20%26quot%3BThese%20headsets%20can%20not%20only%20add%20things%20to%20the%20real%20world%2C%20they%20can%20also%20delete%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Bailenson%20says.%20He%20first%20realized%20VR's%20strange%20editing%20function%20while%20he%20was%20playing%20a%20game%20on%20the%20Quest%203%20that%20%26quot%3Bknocked%20out%26quot%3B%20portions%20of%20the%20real%20walls%20around%20him%20and%20replaced%20them%20with%20a%20virtual%20scene.%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20doing%20VR%20and%20AR%20for%20a%20while%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20I%20had%20never%20in%20my%20life%20seen%20deletion%20work%20so%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%20that%20seems%20pretty%20great.%20Stuck%20on%20a%20crowded%20bus%3F%20Delete%20everyone%20and%20replace%20them%20with%20the%20first-class%20cabin%20of%20a%20jumbo%20jet.%20Hate%20intrusive%20billboards%3F%20Replace%20all%20the%20commercial%20images%20with%20soothing%20vistas%20of%20your%20choosing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221844%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20seated%20using%20an%20Apple%20Vision%20Pro%20headset.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647e289340bf000019fa3d15%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221028%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMaybe%20having%20a%20personal%2C%20editable%20world%20inside%20a%20headset%20will%20be%20cool%20for%20humans%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20not%20so%20great%20for%20humanity.%3Cp%3EApple%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20happens%20when%20the%20technology%20gets%20good%20enough%20to%20delete%2C%20say%2C%20homeless%20people%3F%20Or%20Pride%20flags%3F%20You%20can%20see%20where%20I'm%20going%20here%20%E2%80%94%20literal%20erasure.%20When%20the%20sci-fi%20writer%20William%20Gibson%20came%20up%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20cyberspace%2C%20he%20described%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bconsensual%20hallucination.%26quot%3B%20This%20is%20the%20exact%20opposite%20%E2%80%94%20billions%20of%20discrete%2C%20unshared%20hallucinations%2C%20each%20one%20snowflake-special.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20about%20to%20experience%20is%2C%20using%20these%20headsets%20in%20public%2C%20common%20ground%20disappears%2C%26quot%3B%20Bailenson%20says.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20will%20be%20in%20the%20same%20physical%20place%2C%20experiencing%20simultaneous%2C%20visually%20different%20versions%20of%20the%20world.%20We're%20going%20to%20lose%20common%20ground.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStipulated%3A%20Everyone%20always%20freaks%20out%20about%20new%20consumer%20technology%2C%20and%20the%20freak-out%20is%20almost%20always%20the%20same.%20The%20new%20form%20of%20sensory%20input%20will%20harm%20kids!%20It's%20a%20dangerous%20distraction!%20It's%20socially%20alienating!%20They%20said%20it%20about%20the%20iPhone%2C%20about%20the%20Walkman%20%E2%80%A6%20hell%2C%20half%20a%20millennium%20ago%20they%20said%20it%20about%20the%20book.%20New%20technologies%20arrive%2C%20and%20we%20adapt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20don't%20need%20to%20lean%20hard%20on%20my%20nerdiness%20to%20imagine%20fun%20sci-fi%20uses%20for%20passthrough.%20The%20real%20potential%20here%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20see%20the%20invisible%20informational%20metastructure%20of%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20translation%20overlays%3B%20pop-up%20tags%20that%20display%20people's%20names%20and%20pronouns%20and%20where%20you%20know%20them%20from%3B%20walking%20directions%3B%20user-manual-linked%20X-ray%20vision%20for%20assembling%20an%20Ikea%20coffee%20table.%20Link%20my%20shopping%20list%20to%20the%20aisles%20I%20need%20to%20visit%20in%20the%20supermarket.%20Maybe%20even%20expand%20my%20vision%20beyond%20what%20my%20meatbag%20eyes%20can%20do%2C%20and%20let%20me%20see%20into%20the%20ultraviolet%2C%20or%20perceive%20electrical%20fields.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EPassthrough%20has%20limits%2C%20but%20it%20might%20also%20have%20superpowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20me%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBailenson%20isn't%20a%20freaker-outer%3B%20he%20loves%20VR%2C%20and%20thinks%20the%20new%20headsets%20are%20keen.%20He%20knows%20that%20over%20time%2C%20screens%20will%20get%20better%20resolution%20and%20faster%20rendering.%20New%20algorithms%20will%20minimize%20distortion.%20It's%20not%20the%20technology%20he's%20worried%20about.%20It's%20how%20much%20we're%20going%20to%20become%20immersed%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20world's%20going%20to%20be%20just%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20adapt%20to%20media.%20These%20headsets%20are%20incredible.%20But%20philosophically%2C%20I%20do%20not%20believe%20we%20need%20to%20be%20wearing%20these%20headsets%20for%20hours%20every%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20been%20here%20before%20%E2%80%94%20and%20very%20recently%2C%20at%20that.%20A%20decade%20or%20so%20ago%2C%20no%20one%20paused%20to%20consider%20the%20unintended%20consequences%20of%20thrusting%20millions%20of%20people%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatbots-less-toxic-social-networks-twitter-simulation-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eimpossible-to-moderate%20social%20networks%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20we%20all%20know%20how%20that%20turned%20out.%20Now%2C%20we're%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20sticking%20millions%20of%20people%20into%20helmets%20that%20give%20us%20all%20our%20own%20editable%20realities.%20That's%20why%20the%20kind%20of%20research%20that%20Bailenson%20is%20conducting%20on%20passthrough%20headsets%20is%20so%20important.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20encouraging%20all%20scholars%20to%20act%20with%20some%20urgency%20to%20understand%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20while%20he's%20doing%20his%20work%2C%20maybe%20don't%20forget%20to%20take%20that%20Vision%20Pro%20off%20once%20in%20a%20while.%20The%20longer%20you%20keep%20it%20on%2C%20the%20more%20you're%20turning%20yourself%20into%20a%20human%20guinea%20pig%20%E2%80%94%20one%20with%20really%2C%20really%20bad%20depth%20perception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent