%82GovTech%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%99%AC%20original%20sound%20-%20Symon%C3%A9%E2%80%82B.%E2%80%82%7C%E2%80%82GovTech%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fsection%3E%20%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20government%20jobs%20rely%20on%20technical%20skills%20and%20experience%2C%20rather%20than%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20government%20roles%20may%20not%20require%20degrees%2C%20most%20jobs%20require%20certifications.%20The%20most%20common%20include%20CompTIA%2C%20ISC(2)%2C%20and%20ISACA.%20Some%20roles%20also%20require%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhandbook.tts.gsa.gov%2Fgeneral-information-and-resources%2Fbusiness-and-ops-policies%2Ftop-secret%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBelow%2520are%2520approximate%2520timelines%2520for%2CCompartmented%2520Information%2520(TS%252FSCI)%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclearances%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20take%20up%20to%20several%20months%20to%20get%20approved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20demand%20for%20tech%20continues%2C%20and%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2024%2F01%2F29%2Ffact-sheet-biden-harris-administration-announces-key-ai-actions-following-president-bidens-landmark-executive-order%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTo%2520seize%2520AI%2527s%2520enormous%2520promise%2Ctrain%2520workers%2520with%2520AI%2520expertise.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunches%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20large-scale%20hiring%20initiative%20for%20AI%20specialists%2C%20many%20are%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20break%20into%20the%20business%20without%20paying%20for%20additional%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBenefits%20that%20are%20hard%20to%20pass%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20jobs%20are%20famous%20for%20cushy%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Employee%20Retirement%20System%20(FERS)%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20talked%20about%20benefits%20for%20employees%20working%20in%20the%20government%2C%20although%20government%20contractors%20don't%20offer%20this.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opm.gov%2Fretirement-center%2Ffers-information%2Ftypes-of-retirement%2F%23url%3DOverview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGovernment%3C%2Fa%3E%20pensions%20offer%20retirees%20an%20annual%20income%20after%20they've%20stopped%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20amount%20depends%20on%20how%20many%20years%20an%20employee%20has%20worked%20and%20the%20age%20they're%20retiring%2C%20full%20benefits%20include%2070%25%20of%20an%20annual%20paycheck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20employees%20are%20ever%20in%20crisis%2C%20the%20government%20also%20offers%20EAP%2C%20which%20is%20an%20assistance%20program%20that%20offers%20employees%20legal%20advice%2C%20financial%20advice%2C%20and%20other%20resources%20that%20vary%20on%20the%20state%20or%20federal%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20jobs%20also%20allow%20employees%20to%20travel%20domestically%20and%20abroad.%20Symon%C3%A9%20Berry%2C%20a%20government%20tech%20contractor%2C%20worked%20abroad%20for%20about%20five%20years%20in%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20her%20contract%20work%20abroad%2C%20she%20said%20all%20of%20her%20work-related%20expenses%20were%20paid%2C%20her%20salary%20was%20oftentimes%20untaxed%20due%20to%20agreements%20with%20other%20countries%2C%20and%20she%20received%20travel%20stipends%20dedicated%20to%20%26quot%3Brest%20and%20relaxation%26quot%3B%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20most%20government%20jobs%20provide%20tuition%20assistance%20to%20employees%20at%20a%20standard%20rate%20of%20%24250%20per%20credit%2C%20but%20some%20jobs%20will%20pay%20for%20the%20entire%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexxus%20Harris%2C%20an%20IT%20specialist%20for%20the%20CDC%2C%20said%20that%20her%20education%20was%20free%20because%20her%20schools%20matched%20the%20amount%20the%20government%20provided%20her.%20Harris%20obtained%20two%20degrees%20through%20the%20program%20and%20is%20interested%20in%20getting%20her%20Ph.D.%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20tuition%20assistance%2C%20the%20government%20also%20provides%20student%20loan%20forgiveness%20to%20government%20employees%20after%2010%20years%20of%20making%20payments.%20For%20Tamayo%2C%20this%20is%20the%20largest%20reason%20he%20stays%20in%20the%20public%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20benefits%20like%20these%2C%20the%20potential%20for%20a%20more%20stable%20career%2C%20and%20a%20pension%20waiting%20for%20those%20who%20stick%20it%20out%2C%20it's%20not%20surprising%20that%20people%20are%20finding%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20government%20job%20attractive%20right%20now%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20it%20means%20sacrificing%20the%20higher%20take-home%20pay%20of%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%2C%20social%20media%20is%20their%20starting%20point%20as%20they%20consider%20making%20the%20jump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20scroll%20through%20the%20pages%20of%20more%20than%2012%2C000%20videos%20on%20TikTok%20with%20the%20hashtag%20%26quot%3Bgovernmentjob%2C%26quot%3B%20you'll%20see%20videos%20detailing%20the%20application%20process%2C%20job%20requirements%2C%20and%20the%20experiences%20of%20employees%20in%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-state-government-jobs-trending-tiktok-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707646321000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c54254917a1dae0244aab8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-state-government-jobs-trending-tiktok-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Government%20jobs%20are%20trending%20on%20social%20media%20as%20employees%20seek%20stability%20amid%20mass%20layoffs%20and%20an%20uncertain%20economy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-state-government-jobs-trending-tiktok-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Korean%20celebs%20share%20Lunar%20New%20Year%20wishes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707645856000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107600417%2Cimgsize-37676.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Fkorean-celebrities-share-heartfelt-lunar-new-year-wishes%2Farticleshow%2F107600383.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107600383.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EMusic%20icon%20G-Dragon%20treated%20his%20followers%20on%20Seollal%20with%20a%20visual%20journey%20on%20Instagram.%20He%20shared%20symbolic%20representations%2C%20adorable%20pictures%2C%20and%20a%20poignant%20nod%20to%20the%20unwavering%20support%20from%20his%20fans%2C%20promising%20fresh%20beginnings%20in%20the%20New%20Year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meet%20a%20boomer%20who%20thought%20she'd%20be%20retired%20by%20now%20but%20wants%20to%20help%20her%20millennial%20son%3A%20'I'm%20not%20going%20to%20sit%20back%20and%20watch%20him%20not%20be%20able%20to%20go%20buy%20groceries'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22older%20worker%2C%20boomer%2C%20baby%20boomer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f68cc80323fc4001e0d77a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKelley%20Herford%2C%20not%20pictured%2C%20thought%20she'd%20be%20retired%20by%20now.%3Cp%3ECompassionate%20Eye%20Foundation%2FSteven%20Errico%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKelley%20Herford%2C%2063%2C%20thought%20she'd%20be%20retired%20by%20now.%20Instead%2C%20she's%20still%20working.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHerford%20said%20that%20she%20and%20her%20peers%20did%20everything%20right%20but%20are%20still%20struggling.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELike%20more%20and%20more%20boomers%2C%20she's%20also%20helping%20to%20support%20her%20millennial%20child.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EKelley%20Herford%2C%2063%2C%20thought%20she'd%20be%20retired%20at%20the%20age%20of%2062%2C%20or%20even%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20blessed%2C%20but%20this%20isn't%20what%20I%20expected%20my%20retirement%20years%20and%20pre-retirement%20years%20to%20look%20like%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20drawing%20from%20a%20strong%20pension%20and%20not%20worrying%20about%20anything%20%E2%80%94%20her%20original%20vision%20for%20retirement%20%E2%80%94%20Herford%20is%20still%20punching%20the%20clock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20just%20going%20to%20have%20to%20work%20until%20I%20can't%20work%20any%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerford%20spent%20over%2020%20years%20working%20in%20a%20corporate%20role%2C%20an%20aspect%20of%20the%20boomer%20American%20dream%20that's%20become%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20many%20younger%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20suddenly%20getting%20laid%20off%20and%20having%20to%20weather%20the%20pandemic%20years%20with%20intermittent%20jobs%20and%20underemployment%2C%20Herford%20is%20in%20a%20different%20spot.%20She's%20seen%20her%20IRA%20balance%20go%20down%2C%20dipping%20into%20the%20money%20sooner%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20never%20expected%20something%20like%20that%20to%20come%20along%20where%20I%20couldn't%20work%20for%20a%20few%20years%20even%20doing%20nominal%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20I%20was%20living%20off%20of%20my%20savings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerford%20said%20she%20is%20one%20of%20a%20generation%20who%20did%20what%20they%20were%20supposed%20to%20do%20to%20get%20ahead%20%E2%80%94%20go%20to%20school%2C%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20and%20establish%20a%20career.%20But%20not%20all%20of%20them%20feel%20it's%20paid%20off%20in%20the%20way%20they'd%20hoped.%20Indeed%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-not-enough-retirement-savings-gen-z-millennials-eldercare-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBI's%20Ann%20C.%20Logue%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20boomers%20aren't%20financially%20equipped%20to%20retire%20right%20now%2C%20with%20a%20solid%20chunk%20holding%20no%20retirement%20savings%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncoa.org%2Farticle%2Fget-the-facts-on-economic-security-for-seniors%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eover%2017%20million%20Americans%20over%20the%20age%20of%2065%20considered%20economically%20insecure%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20everything%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Herford%20said.%20She%20remembers%20being%20told%20that%2C%20as%20a%20woman%2C%20things%20were%20better%20than%20they%20ever%20used%20to%20be%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20she%20was%20earning%20less.%20She%20said%20she%20was%20told%2C%20%26quot%3BDon't%20ever%20rely%20on%20a%20man%2C%20and%20get%20your%20education%2C%20and%20stay%20with%20the%20same%20company%20and%20work%20hard%20and%20they'll%20reward%20you.%20And%20my%20girlfriends%20and%20I%2C%20we%20all%20took%20that%20to%20heart.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIf%20it's%20bad%20for%20boomers%2C%20it's%20worse%20for%20their%20millennial%20kids%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20Herford%20works%20as%20a%20nanny%20%E2%80%94%20a%20job%20she%20feels%20fortunate%20to%20have.%20She%20was%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20in%20Charleston%2C%20South%20Carolina%2C%20with%20a%20good%20interest%20rate.%20It's%20an%20area%20with%20opportunities%20for%20work%2C%20and%20has%20lower%20taxes%20and%20cost%20of%20living%20than%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20area%20where%20she%20previously%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20thought%20she'd%20have%20more%20of%20a%20cushion%20after%20she%20spent%20years%20saving%20a%20good%20chunk%20of%20her%20pre-tax%20income%20%E2%80%94%20she%20said%20she%20saved%2015%25%20of%20it%20while%20also%20raising%20a%20child%20in%20a%20single-income%20household.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20always%20worked%20on%20the%20weekends%20doing%20whatever%20I%20could%20do%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20maintained%20my%20savings%2C%20thinking%20that%20if%20I%20had%20over%20a%20million%20dollars%2C%20I'd%20be%20set%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20she%20said%2C%20she's%20%26quot%3Bhanging%20in%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20can't%20travel.%20Her%20few%20splurges%20are%20continuing%20to%20have%20some%20streaming%20platforms%2C%20although%20she's%20cut%20out%20a%20few%20of%20those.%20She%20doesn't%20eat%20out.%20She%20tries%20not%20to%20touch%20her%20savings%20unless%20it's%20money%20she%20needs%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20everything%20right%20and%20it%20was%20like%20we%20were%20treading%20backwards%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20going%20backwards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerford%20is%20also%2C%20like%20many%20parents%2C%20feeling%20the%20squeeze%20from%20both%20sides%3A%20She's%20trying%20to%20stay%20afloat%2C%20and%20she's%20also%20trying%20to%20ensure%20her%20kid%20does%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20situation%20that's%20becoming%20more%20common%2C%20as%20more%20parents%20support%20their%20young%20adult%20children.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2024%2F01%2F25%2Fparents-young-adult-children-and-the-transition-to-adulthood%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erecent%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%203%2C017%20adults%20and%201%2C495%20young%20adults%2C%20conducted%20in%20October%20and%20November%202022%2C%20found%20that%2059%25%20of%20parents%20with%20kids%20ages%2018%20to%2034%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-parents-give-gen-z-millennial-kids-financial-assistance-pew-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efinancially%20assisted%20them%20in%20the%20last%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20turn%2C%20just%2045%25%20of%20young%20adults%20in%20that%20age%20bracket%20said%20that%20they%20were%20completely%20financially%20independent%20from%20their%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20help%20my%20son%20and%20I'll%20help%20him%20as%20long%20as%20I%20can%20because%20these%20millennials%2C%20if%20they%20don't%20get%20together%20and%20have%20roommates%20or%20spouses%2C%20they're%20scraping%20by%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20He%20lived%20with%20her%20briefly%20post-grad%2C%20and%20she%20still%20helps%20him%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20there%20may%20be%20criticism%20over%20older%20parents%20helping%20out%20their%20children%2C%20Herford%20asks%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20we%20supposed%20to%20do%3F%20These%20kids%20came%20into%20a%20time%20when%20corporations%20are%20only%20rewarding%20people%20at%20the%20top.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerford%20said%20she%20just%20doesn't%20know%20%26quot%3Bhow%20these%20kids%20are%20going%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%20They're%20not%20making%20enough%20money%2C%20they're%20burdened%20with%20student%20loan%20debt%2C%20and%20just%20barely%20scraping%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYes%2C%20boomer%20parents%20are%20helping%20them%20and%20maybe%20it%20will%20upset%20our%20retirement%20plans%2C%20but%20what%20are%20we%20supposed%20to%20do%3F%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20sit%20back%20and%20watch%20him%20not%20be%20able%20to%20go%20buy%20groceries%20because%20the%20cost%20of%20everything%20is%20just%20completely%20out%20of%20control%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20corporations%20are%20being%20very%20greedy.%20I%20think%20everyone%20raised%20their%20prices%20because%20they%20could%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20it's%20going%20to%20stop.%20It's%20just%20a%20travesty.%20It's%20really%2C%20really%2C%20really%20scary.%26quot%3B%3C%2F