cientists-disagree-about-drivers-of-septembers-temperature-spike%2F%5C%22%3Efar%20beyond%3C%2Fa%3E%20what%20we%20consider%20%E2%80%98normal.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20crazy%20as%20the%20weather%20has%20been%2C%20we%20are%20sure%20to%20see%20worse%20in%20the%20years%20ahead.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.ametsoc.org%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fclim%2F35%2F3%2FJCLI-D-21-0200.1.xml%5C%22%3Efrequency%2C%20extent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20intensity%20of%20such%20severe%20weather%20is%20increasing%20due%20to%20global%20warming%20caused%20by%20the%20accumulation%20of%20excess%20greenhouse%20gasses%20(GHGs)%20%E2%80%93%20like%20carbon%20dioxide%20and%20methane%20%E2%80%93%20that%20trap%20heat%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%20These%20excess%20GHGs%20result%20directly%20from%20industrial%20and%20other%20economic%20activities%20linked%20to%20burning%20fossil%20fuels%20and%20destroying%20forests%20and%20wetlands.%20The%20excess%20heat%20they%20trap%20is%20causing%20the%20ice%20to%20rapidly%20melt%20away%20from%20the%20Arctic%20Ocean%20and%20Greenland%2C%20exposing%20dark%20waters%20and%20rock%20surfaces%20that%20directly%20absorb%20even%20more%20solar%20radiation%3B%20this%20then%20drives%20its%20own%20contribution%20to%20further%20warming%20%E2%80%93%20and%20thus%20further%20melting%20%E2%80%93%20in%20what%E2%80%99s%20called%20an%20%3Cem%3Eamplifying%20feedback%20loop%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20one%20of%20several%20in%20the%20climate%20system.%20Over%20the%20coming%20decades%2C%20the%20lists%20of%20nations%20and%20cities%20hit%20by%20floods%20will%20grow%20longer%2C%20the%20heatwave%20death%20tolls%20more%20harrowing%2C%20the%20crop%20losses%20much%20higher.%20This%20much%20we%20already%20know%20will%20happen%2C%20as%20the%20globe%20continues%20to%20warm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%