0IPCC%20publishes%20major%20technical%20reports%20detailing%20the%20state%20of%20global%20GHG%20emissions%2C%20with%20a%20strong%20focus%20on%20carbon-dioxide%2C%20describing%20how%20this%20might%20affect%20the%20climate%2C%20different%20ecosystems%2C%20and%20civilisational%20infrastructures%20now%20and%20in%20the%20future.%20They%20outline%20a%20range%20of%20theoretical%20scenarios%20to%20guide%20governments%20and%20other%20institutions%20as%20they%20set%20targets%20to%20reduce%20fossil%20fuel%20burning%2C%20forest%20and%20wetland%20degradation%2C%20and%20other%20activities%20that%20directly%20contribute%20to%20the%20accumulation%20of%20atmospheric%20GHGs.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipcc.ch%2Fsite%2Fassets%2Fuploads%2Fsites%2F2%2F2022%2F06%2FSPM_version_report_LR.pdf%5C%22%3EThey%E2%80%99ve%20determined%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20that%20the%20average%20global%20temperature%20is%20likely%20to%20rise%20by%201.5%C2%BAC%20between%202030%E2%80%932053%2C%20relative%20to%20what%20it%20was%20before%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution%20%E2%80%93%20a%20threshold%20nearly%20touched%20already%20in%202023%2C%20when%20the%20globe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwmo.int%2Fmedia%2Fnews%2Fwmo-confirms-2023-smashes-global-temperature-record%5C%22%3Ewarmed%20by%201.45%C2%BAC%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%93%20quantifying%20and%20describing%20the%20extreme%20threats%20that%20lie%20beyond%20this%20temperature%20threshold.%20These%20findings%20have%20put%20pressure%20on%20governments%20to%20make%20pledges%20about%20lowering%20carbon%20dioxide%20emissions%20within%20their%20borders.%20Perhaps%20the%20IPCC%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20triumph%20is%20in%20helping%20to%20shift%20the%20global%20conversation%20on%20climate%20justice%20and%20equitability%2C%20finally%20establishing%20the%20need%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98loss%20and%20damage%20fund%2C%E2%80%99%20whereby%20wealthier%20nations%20%E2%80%93%20who%20have%20historically%20contributed%20the%20far%20greater%20share%20of%20GHGs%20